import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.hist(data['values'], bins=20, color='blue', alpha=0.7, label='Values')
    plt.axvline(data['values'].median(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=2, label=f"Median: {data['values'].median():.2f}")
    plt.xlabel('Values')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of values in the Volcano Dataset?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.scatter(data['width'], data['height'], c=data['values'], cmap='viridis')
    plt.xlabel('Width')
    plt.ylabel('Height')
    plt.title('Is there a correlation between the width and height of the volcano?', wrap=True)
    plt.colorbar(label='Values')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    ax.boxplot(data['values'])
    avg_value = data['values'].mean()
    ax.axhline(avg_value, color='r', linestyle='--', label=f'Average: {avg_value:.2f}')
    plt.title('What is the average value of the volcano?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Values')
    plt.ylabel('Distribution')
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    ax.boxplot(data['values'])
    ax.set_title('What is the range of values in the Volcano Dataset?')
    ax.set_ylabel('Values')
    ax.set_xticklabels(['Volcano'])
    
    min_value = data['values'].min()
    max_value = data['values'].max()
    
    ax.axhline(min_value, color='red', linestyle='--', label=f'Min: {min_value:.2f}')
    ax.axhline(max_value, color='green', linestyle='--', label=f'Max: {max_value:.2f}')
    ax.legend()
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
